1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">We live in =
a world of diametrically opposed forces: The U.S. isn&#8217;t just more con=
servative, it&#8217;s more conservative <em>and</em> more liberal. The wedd=
ing industry is bigger than ever, and at the same time, more Americans than=
 ever question the institution of marriage. &#8220;One group seeks more tec=
hnology, another wants to sit in the Amtrak Quiet Car,&#8221; Penn writes. =
